# Typing Rules

- Always use modern typing syntax (e.g., `list` instead of `List`, `dict` instead of `Dict`)
- Import types from the `typing` module when needed
- Use type hints for all function parameters and return values
- Use `Optional[T]` instead of `Union[T, None]`
- Use `list[T]`, `dict[K, V]`, `set[T]` instead of `List[T]`, `Dict[K, V]`, `Set[T]`
- Always include type annotations for class attributes
- Use `Any` sparingly and document why it's necessary
- Prefer `Protocol` over `ABC` for structural typing
- Use `Literal` for string/enum-like values
- Use `TypedDict` for dictionary structures with known keys
